<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
99. 
<taxonomicName LSID="28950B14-5640-5D32-8240-9D1E3B41EC2B" authority="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 520)." authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus subspathulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subspathulatus">Convolvulus subspathulatus Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke 1882: 520).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Type.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
SOMALIA, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Hildebrandt</emphasis>
1312 (holotype B†).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
Perennial herb with prostrate or twining stems to 50 cm long, vegetative parts densely sericeous becoming golden-brown when old. Leaves shortly petiolate, 0.6-2 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
0.6-2 cm, suborbicular, apex rounded or, rarely, emarginate or obtuse, base cordate, margin entire; petioles 1-6 mm long. Flowers 2-5 in shortly pedunculate, bracteate heads; peduncles 0.4-1.5 cm; bracteoles 7-10 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
5-7 mm, oblong-elliptic to ovate; outer sepals 5-7 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 mm, oblong to obovate, villous; corolla 9-11 mm long, blue, unlobed, midpetaline bands pilose; ovary glabrous; style glabrous, divided 3 mm above base; stigmas 1.75-2 mm, narrowly cylindrical and thicker than style. Capsule glabrous; seeds glabrous, tuberculate. [
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin 2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235]
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
Endemic to Somalia (
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Thulin &amp; Warfa</emphasis>
4533, 5907; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Friis et al</emphasis>
. 5024; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Revoil</emphasis>
s.n. [6/1883], 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Tardelli &amp; Bavazzano</emphasis>
502). On coastal sand dunes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="125" pageNumber="126" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="125" pageNumber="126">
<bibRefCitation author="Thulin, M" journalOrPublisher="Flora of Somalia" pageId="212" pageNumber="213" pagination="232 - 237" refId="B360" refString="Thulin, M, 2006. Convolvulus. Flora of Somalia volume 3: 232 - 237" title="Convolvulus." volume="volume 3" year="2006">Thulin (2006</bibRefCitation>
: 235) suggests that this species is scarcely different from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verdc., Kew Bull. 12: 344. 1957. (Verdcourt" authorityYear="1957" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus jefferyi" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="jefferyi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Convolvulus jefferyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and his description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vatke, Linnaea 43: 519. 1882. (Vatke" authorityYear="1882" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Convolvulus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Convolvulus subspathulatus" order="Solanales" pageId="125" pageNumber="126" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subspathulatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Convolvulus subspathulatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="125" pageNumber="126">Flora of Somalia</emphasis>
seems to anticipate uniting the two species. However the suborbicular leaf shape and sericeous indumentum serve to distinguish the two species easily.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
